        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(discord): gate native built-ins before success UI",
        "body": "Closes #86654\n\n## Summary\n- gate native Discord built-in commands through the stricter owner allowlist auth path before menu/success UI is shown\n- avoid optimistic command-arg success messaging by changing `Selected ...` to `Applying ...`\n- add a regression test for the native slash `ownerAllowFrom` rejection path\n\n## Root cause\nThe native Discord built-in command flow could acknowledge a selection before the downstream built-in auth path had actually accepted the directive. When that later auth rejected the directive, the interaction could fall through to the generic `✅ Done.` fallback, while the target session state stayed unchanged.\n\n## Test evidence\n- `pnpm vitest run extensions/discord/src/monitor/native-command.commands-allowfrom.test.ts extensions/discord/src/monitor/native-command.options.test.ts extensions/discord/src/monitor/native-command.plugin-dispatch.test.ts extensions/discord/src/monitor/native-command.think-autocomplete.test.ts`\n- result: 31/31 tests passing\n\n## Rollback\nRevert this PR to restore the previous native built-in command flow and picker copy.\n",
